With instances of rain across parts of Mpumalanga last night and this morning, February 17, the Kruger National Park’s Disaster Management Team said it is expecting more showers throughout the day. SANParks said the rain will delay the process of assessing damage to the road infrastructure and restrict movement for visitors. ALSO READ: Address power outage issues or we go off the grid, warns Kruger Lowveld Chamber of Business and Tourism “Indications are that gravel roads in the south will remain closed. Lower Sabie to Skukuza will also remain closed for repairs,” said the statement. The park urged visitors to be cautious when crossing low-lying bridges. It said the rainfall forecast predicts moderate rain over very wet catchment areas, and this may result in some localised impacts.